@startuml "JOB_CHECK_INTERVAL: 250ms Periodic Checking"
title "Background Job Checking: 250ms Interval Strategy"

' ==================== CONSTANTS ====================

note as ConstantsNote
  **Source: src/main.rs (lines 17-25)**

  const JOB_CHECK_INTERVAL: Duration = Duration::from_millis(250);

  **Why 250ms?**
  - Human perception threshold: users perceive <300ms as "instant"
  - Job completion feels immediate to user
  - Sweet spot between responsiveness and lock contention
  - Avoids querying on every keystroke
  - Typical typing rate: ~50-100ms between keystrokes
    (won't check on every keystroke)
  - Low-activity periods: <300ms detection feels smooth
end note

' ==================== MAIN EVENT LOOP TIMING ====================

participant "Event Loop" as Loop
participant "time tracking\n(last_job_check: Instant)" as Tracker
participant "timeout select\n(100ms timeout)" as Timeout
participant "check_completed_jobs()" as Checker
participant "UI render" as Render

